The schema already has `event`, so the cheapest faithful choice is prompt-only: one-off actions and plans should be extracted as dated/session-anchored events when useful, never rewritten as global preferences or routines. Because the extractor is LLM-backed, the automated regression will enforce the exact prompt contract and fixture wiring; I’ll also add an opt-in manual evaluation that runs those fixtures through the real Claude-backed extraction path and checks the semantic outputs.
